Package org.gradoop.flink.algorithms.gelly.functions

Contains common functions used to map Gradoop to Gelly graphs.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    EdgeToGellyEdge<EV>
    Convert a Gradoop Edge to a Gelly Edge.
    ElementToGellyEdge<I,K,EV>
    Convert class I to a Gelly Edge with K key and EV value.
    ElementToGellyVertex<I,K,VV>
    Convert class I to a Gelly Vertex with K key and VV value.
    VertexToGellyVertex<VV>
    Convert a Gradoop Vertex to a Gelly Vertex.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    EdgeToGellyEdgeWithDouble
    Maps EPGM edge to a Gelly edge consisting of EPGM source and target identifier and Double as edge value.
    EdgeToGellyEdgeWithNullValue
    Maps EPGM edge to a Gelly edge consisting of EPGM source and target identifier and NullValue as edge value.
    EdgeToGellyEdgeWithPropertyValue
    Maps EPGM edge to a Gelly edge consisting of EPGM source and target identifier and PropertyValue as edge value.
    LongTupleToGellyEdgeWithLongValue
    Map function to create gelly edge from long tuple.
    LongTupleToGellyVertexWithLongValue
    Map function to create gelly vertices from long tuple.
    VertexToGellyVertexWithGradoopId
    Maps EPGM vertex to a Gelly vertex with the GradoopId as its id and value.
    VertexToGellyVertexWithNullValue
    Maps EPGM vertex to a Gelly vertex with the GradoopId as its id.
    VertexToGellyVertexWithPropertyValue
    Maps EPGM vertex to a Gelly vertex consisting of the EPGM identifier and a PropertyValue.
    WritePropertyToGraphHeadMap
    MapFunction, that writes a given property value to the GraphHead.

Package org.gradoop.flink.algorithms.gelly.functions Description

Contains common functions used to map Gradoop to Gelly graphs.
